abstract: The senior pastor of Ebenezer Baptist Church, the Rev. Dr. Raphael G. Warnock, may be helped in Georgia by his religiosity, but his liberal positions could turn off some voters.
snippet: The senior pastor of Ebenezer Baptist Church, the Rev. Dr. Raphael G. Warnock, may be helped in Georgia by his religiosity, but his liberal positions could turn off some voters.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Ebenezer Baptist Church bills itself as “America’s Freedom Church,” a reflection of its lofty stature as the house of worship where the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. once preached. Over the decades, the 6,000-member congregation just east of downtown Atlanta has become a favored stop for national politicians seeking to make their case to the African-American community and pay homage to the slain civil rights icon.

abstract: Four Democratic presidential candidates hoping for success in the state remained in Washington for President Trump’s Senate trial.
snippet: Four Democratic presidential candidates hoping for success in the state remained in Washington for President Trump’s Senate trial.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Four Democratic presidential candidates hoping for breakout performances in the Iowa caucuses next week spent Thursday in Washington listening to questioning in the Senate impeachment trial of President Trump.

abstract: The fate of his memoir is up to government censors. That’s troubling.
snippet: The fate of his memoir is up to government censors. That’s troubling.
lead_paragraph: Thanks to a leak to the press, we all now know that John Bolton has written an explosive account of President Trump’s fateful decision to withhold hundreds of millions of dollars in security assistance from Ukraine. But it is far from clear how much of this story the public will be permitted to read, and when.

snippet: The number, which has steadily increased since the Jan. 8 attack, is now at 64.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Defense Department said on Thursday that 64 troops had sustained traumatic brain injuries after the Iranian ballistic missile strikes on Ayn Al Asad Air Base in Iraq this month, up 14 from an earlier announcement this week.

abstract: A second day of questions revealed little. On Friday, things get interesting.
snippet: A second day of questions revealed little. On Friday, things get interesting.
lead_paragraph: At the risk of sounding critical, the second day of Q. & A. in the Senate’s impeachment trial of President Trump was less than illuminating — perhaps even the teensiest bit tedious.

abstract: The double-barreled tactic of sending medicine to Iranians and penalizing its leaders is an effort to fuel frustration against the government in Tehran.
snippet: The double-barreled tactic of sending medicine to Iranians and penalizing its leaders is an effort to fuel frustration against the government in Tehran.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Thursday piled new economic sanctions onto its ever-growing pressure campaign against Iran, but it also opened access to medicine for cancer and organ transplant patients in an effort to turn Iranians against their leaders.
